history.text: Hello, have you seen Monsters University?
I have but it has been awhile. It was a good movie.
Yeah, it was a decent sequel to the original.
Yeah. It is Disney movie and they usually do a good job with their movies.
Yeah, it has pretty good scores. Rotten tomatoes gave it a 79%
Yeah. For a comedy-animation film, they did a good job making it a funny squeal with good animation.
Yeah, Billy Crystal and John Goodman have great chemistry
Yeah. They do and Dan Scanlon did a good job directing it as well.
Yeah, I agree. It's true to the spirit of the original Monsters Inc., but it still feels new
Yeah. It is a cute movie that is funny and has colorful animation.
Mike Wazowski is so cute as a little monster, I love that they showed his journey
Yeah. I like how you get to see how he met his friend Sulley.
Yeah, I like how they show their progression into friendship. Sulley is a really privileged student and doesn't have to try and it's cool to see his connection to mike.
Yeah. It is fun to see them try to join a fraternity but only Sulley is accepted.

I like the Dean's character played by Helen Mir
ren as well. I thought she was a good addition.
Yeah. I also like the character of Squishy that is played by Peter Sohn.
The whole scare games sequence is really fun too
It makes the stakes higher when they make a deal that if they loose they have to leave the university.
Yeah. I like that Mike enters the Scare Games by joining the Oozma Kappa team, the weakest fraternity on campus.

Right. It's a little sad when you figure out he only won the scare portion because
 Sulley had to tamper with the machine.
Yeah but it is fun to see how they improved up to that point with the help of Mike and his training and knowledge of scaring.
Yeah, it shows he knows how it's executed just that he can't physically do it.
I liked also seeing Randal as a nerdy sort of character, voiced by Steve Buscemi
Yeah. For a film that came out in 2013 it has enough of the stuff you need to make it haunt the imagination long after the buzz of its fluffy-furred cutness has gone away.
I was glad to see the other students in Oozma Kappa are accepted into the scare program
Yeah and that Hardscrabble praises Sully and Mike and says that they were the first students to surprise her.
I like that they took regular jobs in the mailroom in Monsters Inc.
Yeah which leads them to finally join the scarer team and up to were the first movie starts.
Right, i thought it was cool that they did a prequel instead of a sequel
It was a good prequel overall and that also got a CinemaScore of an A.
